    "shortDescription": "Red-eyed tree frogs are bright green climbers from the forests of Central America and northwestern South America. They sleep tucked against leaves, hiding their flashy blue-and-yellow sides, orange feet, and red eyes until danger gets too close. Fun fact: They are not poisonous — the sudden burst of color is a startle trick that may buy the frog a split second to leap away."
